To build the "messages.c" program, which implements processes with the message queue, enter the command 

gcc -g -lpthread -lm -lrt -o x messages.c helpers.c

on a linux command line with gcc installed, where "x" is the desired executable name. 


To build the "threads.c" program, which implements threads with shared memory, enter the command 

gcc -g -lpthread -lm -lrt -o x threads.c helpers.c

on a linux command line with gcc installed, where "x" is the desired executable name. 